TensorFlow Code (Voice Recognition):

For voice recognition, you can use TensorFlow to train a model that recognizes specific voice commands. Here's an example code that shows how to train a TensorFlow model to recognize the voice command "turn on the LED":
```python
import tensorflow as tf
import librosa

# Load audio file
audio_file = '/path/to/turn_on_led.wav'
audio, sample_rate = librosa.load(audio_file)

# Extract features
mfccs = librosa.feature.mfcc(y=audio, sr=sample_rate, n_mfcc=13)
mfccs = mfccs.reshape(1, -1)

# Load model
model = tf.keras.models.load_model('/path/to/model.h5')

# Predict label
label = model.predict(mfccs)[0]
if label == 1:
  print('The voice command is "turn on the LED"')

```
This code loads an audio file that contains the voice command "turn on the LED", extracts features using the librosa library, and predicts the label using a pre-trained TensorFlow model.

